<P>
   1. THREE LITTLE BOYS, THREE LITTLE GRAVES, AN UNENDING TRAGEDY
The nightmare in Northern Ireland never ends. Every horrific
bombing underscores a centuries-old religious division that
political will has yet to mend. The Quinn family knows the violence
all too well. In July, three young brothers, Richard, Mark and
Jason Quinn, died in the first major terrorist attack since the
Good Friday peace accord. In this moving interview, their mother,
