Slobodian. From The Calgary Sun. 2,000 words. 2. HOW MUCH OF
POLITICS IS ENTERTAINMENT? Have we reached the point where the line
between entertainment and news is blurring? Like entertainment,
politics is increasingly part of the easy-listening background
music of the time. More and more, politicians play to the camera.
There's nothing entertaining about Bill Clinton's plight since the
Monica Lewinsky story broke in January - and yet the entire
spectacle has more in common with mass entertainment than with
serious politics. By David M. Shribman. From The Boston Globe
Magazine. 2,500 words. 3. RAIDING THE TOY CHESTS Today's kids are
