<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Bengals picks 'surprise' Brown
 &HT;    By Chick Ludwig
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   CINCINNATI, Ohio _ When he saw Stepfret Williams' name on the
waiver wire, Bengals president Mike Brown was surprised.
</P>
<P>
   Enamored with Williams' speed, Brown claimed the former Dallas
wide receiver recently. To make room on the 53-man roster, the
Bengals waived first-year wideout Chris Doering.
</P>
<P>
   Williams, a 6-foot, 170-pound, third-year veteran from Northeast
Louisiana, had 31 catches for 340 yards and a touchdown for Dallas
from 1996 to '97.
</P>
<P>
   He played in all five 1998 preseason games, compiling six
catches for 69 yards, six kickoff returns for 151 yards and two
punt returns for 14 yards.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's quick and fast,'' Brown said. ``He helps on punt returns.
We think he can be a solid backup here behind Carl (Pickens) and
Darnay (Scott), and compete for the third spot with (David) Dunn
and (James) Hundon.
</P>
<P>
   ``I see names on the waiver wire from time to time that surprise
me. I wouldn't have predicted that he'd end up here a few weeks
ago, but that's how it worked out.''
</P>
<P>
   Doering, a former Florida star whose 31 TD catches are a
Southeastern Conference record, led the Bengals in preseason
receiving yards with 127 on six catches.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
