   &UR; Swissair Crash &LR;  (``a'' code)
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times plans this package of stories on the Swissair
crash off Nova Scotia.
</P>
<P>
   CRASH-RDP (Undated) _ Ledeall on the crash Wednesday night off
Nova Scotia of a Swissair jet en route from New York to Geneva. All
229 people aboard were killed. By Robert D. McFadden.
</P>
<P>
   With photo and graphic.
</P>
<P>
   CRASH-INQUIRY (Undated) _ Developments in the investigation into
the cause of the crash, and a look at the plane, an MD-11. By
Matthew L. Wald.
</P>
<P>
   CRASH-TOWN (Peggy's Cove, N.S.) _ A small, touristy fishing
village is upended by the air disaster. By Carey Goldberg.
</P>
<P>
   CRASH-RESCUE (Undated) _ The search for bodies and debris in the
Atlantic.
</P>
<P>
   CRASH-VICTIMS (Undated) _ A look at who was on board the fatal
flight. By N.R. Kleinfield.
</P>
<P>
   CRASH-FAMILIES (Geneva, Switzerland) _ The scene in Geneva,
families of passengers react to the news. By John Tagliabue.
</P>
<P>
   CRASH-OBIT-MANN (Boston) _ Obituary of Dr. Jonathan Mann, a
pioneer in AIDS research and former head of the WHO Global Program
on AIDS who died in the Swiss Air crash. By Philip J. Hilts. (1200
words)
</P>
<P>
   In addition, the Boston Globe plans a lengthy takeout on Dr.
Mann, the AIDS researcher by Richard A. Knox of the Globe science
desk.
