3, 1998. IF YOU HAVE ANY QUESTIONS, PLEASE CALL US AT 202-628-3100.
<TEXT>
<P>
   CONNECTICUT -- LIEBERMAN. Sen. Joseph I. Lieberman is expected
to give a floor speech about his reaction to President Clinton's
admission of an improper relationship with Monica Lewinsky. Maggi
</P>
<P>
   FLORIDA -- STEARNS. U.S. Rep. Cliff Stearns called on President
Clinton to resign in the wake of his public admission that he lied
to the nation about his relationship with Monica Lewinsky. Williams
</P>
<P>
   INDIANA -- O'BANNON. Two years after upsetting Republican
Stephen Goldsmith, Gov. Frank O'Bannon (D) pulled off another upset
of sorts, winning praise from a conservative economic policy group
for his fiscal decisions. Wolfberg
</P>
<P>
   LOUISIANA -- PORK-DEFENSE. Louisiana will receive nearly $40
million if President Clinton signs the military construction
appropriations bill that passed in the Senate Tuesday. The spending
items have been criticized as pork, but the Louisiana delegation
thinks they are essential. Stricherz
</P>
<P>
   MARYLAND -- SIERRA. The Sierra Club began an ad campaign to
educate voters about their congressperson's voting record on the
environment, and Rep. Connie Morella is one of few Republicans to
make the grade with the pro-environmental organization (Brief.)
Brown
</P>
<P>
   MASSACHUSETTS -- FEC. Follow on latest campaign fund-raising and
spending reports from Massachusetts' 8th Congressional District.
(Working.) Williams
