<P>
   OHIO -- DEBT. (RE-SEND with comments from Rep. LaTourette.) More
and more Americans, and Ohioans, are going bankrupt. On Friday, the
Senate is expected to take a step toward making it harder to erase
debt. But the details of the bill and how it was influenced remain
unclear. Stricherz
</P>
<P>
   -- FEDERAL-FUNDS. Ohio received 93 cents for every tax dollar
sent to Washington in 1997 -- one of the lowest levels in the last
10 years -- according to a report released Tuesday by the
Northeast-Midwest Institute. The state ranks 41st in per-capita
federal spending. Will include county-specific numbers. Hurt
</P>
<P>
   -- TURNOUT-DEMS. Political analysts say that what was originally
going to be a challenging year for Ohio Democrats may turn into a
downright electoral disaster. The key will be turnout, and analysts
say the combination of President Clinton's problems, the inability
of Dem Sen. John Glenn to campaign and a strong Republican ticket
could keep Ohio Democrats home on Nov. 3. Eckstein
</P>
<P>
   -- POLL. A poll detailing Ohio residents' opinions on campaign
finance reform will be released today by campaign reform activists.
(Possible.) Gorman
</P>
<P>
   -- VOINOVICH. A Libertarian think tank takes aim at Republican
Gov. George Voinovich's fiscal policy, calling him the most
``fiscally liberal Republican governor in America.'' (Possible --
awaiting response from Voinovich.) Gorman
</P>
<P>
   VIRGIN ISLANDS -- GOV. Two years ago, with tuxedoed waiters
catering and a steel band entertaining, about 100 people welcomed
the opening of a new Virgin Islands governor's Washington office
with great fanfare. Today, the front door to the office is
sometimes locked during business hours, while telephone calls
frequently go unreturned. Williams
</P>
<P>
   WISCONSIN -- SENSENBRENNER. He's the most senior member of the
Wisconsin delegation and has not faced major opposition in an
election since 1978. Rep. Jim Sensenbrenner, R-Wis., will play a
pivotal role in the upcoming impeachment inquiry of President
Clinton as a member of the Judiciary Committee. (Working.) Marlin
</P>
