<P>
   DRESS-CODE _ AUSTIN, Texas _ An untucked shirt can be a high
school teen-ager's fashion trademark. But to a school administrator
in a society of deadly school shootings, it could be the cover for
a dangerous weapon. The two views of an untucked shirt collided
recently at Bastrop High School, where school officials' insistence
that all shirts be tucked clashed with some students' drive for
individualism. The result: More than 200 of the school's 1,500
students walked out of class. (Rodriguez, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   OHIO-TREES _ Trees are like a business facing a shortage of raw
materials, said Woody Wesig of Woody Tree Medics, and right now
some are on short work weeks and some are going bankrupt. ``On a
scale of 10, a brown leaf is zero, and a bright green is a Madonna
10,'' said Wesig. ``We're not seeing too many 10s right now. Many
trees are around five.'' There are many reasons that trees are
losing leaves early this year: too much rain earlier and too little
lately. (Dempsey, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
