<SLUG> BC-BOOKS-GUESTPICKS-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    LOOKING FORWARD TO ...what readers in metro Atlanta are talking
about for the fall
 &HT;    (EMBARGOED UNTIL SEPTEMBER 6: DO NOT USE BEFORE THEN)
 &HT;    By Don O'Briant and Teresa K. Weaver
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   PEARL CLEAGE, author of ``What Looks Like Crazy on an Ordinary
Day''
</P>
<P>
   ``Alice Walker's new novel is my hot title this fall. I can't
wait.''
</P>
<P>
   ELIZABETH WILSON, spokeswoman for Chapter 11 bookstores:
``Besides all the obvious ones, I think the Lindbergh biography by
Scott Berg is going to be very big. And `Rocket Boys' by Homer
Hickam is a great read.'' Other titles to look for: ``The Tennis
Partner'' by Abraham Verghese, ``The Professor and the Madman'' by
Simon Winchester (``an extraordinary book'') and Peter Jennings'
``The Century.'' ``And, of course, everybody's talking about Tom
Wolfe. ...''
</P>
<P>
   MELISSA FAY GREENE, author of ``The Temple Bombing'':
``Definitely the Philip Roth novel `I Married a Communist' and
Alexander Solzhenitsyn's `November 1916.'''
</P>
<P>
   LEE WALBURN, editor in chief of Atlanta magazine: ``I'm looking
forward to reading (the paperback reprint of) `Home Fires Burning'
by Robert Inman. And, like everybody else, I want to read Tom
Wolfe's `A Man in Full.'''
</P>
<P>
   FRANK REISS, owner of A Cappella Books .``Obviously, there's a
buzz about Tom Wolfe's new book. A couple that I'm really looking
forward to are Michael Chabon's `Werewolves in Their Youth' and
Ethan Canin's `For Kings and Planets.' He's another really good
writer we haven't heard from in a while.''
</P>
<P>
   E. LYNN HARRIS, author of ``If This World Were Mine'': ``I'm
looking forward to reading `Stigmata' by Phyllis Perry, of course.
And I want to read `The Wake of the Wind' by J. California Cooper
and `Something's Wrong With My Scale' by Van Whitfield.''
</P>
<P>
   PAUL COSSMAN, president of Humpus Bumpus bookstore . ```The
First Horseman' by John Case is a biomedical thriller ... that has
what everybody wants these days.'' Other picks for fall: ``The
Children's Civil War'' by James Marten, the Georgia Conservancy's
``Highroad Guide to the Georgia Mountains'' and the Reader's Digest
``Book of Birds.''
</P>
<P>
   FREDERICK ALLEN, author of ``Atlanta Rising'': ``I'm curious
about `Dutch,' Edmund Morris' biography of Ronald Reagan. He's a
really good writer. And I want to read Tom Wolfe's `A Man in
Full.'''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
