<P>
   FBC-UGA-TECH _ After months of waiting, Georgia and Georgia Tech
finally open the 1998 college football season. As both teams head
into their home opener, there are several questions in both camps
-- Can Georgia replace quarterback Mike Bobo and several key
offensive personnel and can Tech strengthen a defense that was the
worst in the ACC last year? The first tests appear to be easy for
both teams as Georgia hosts Kent and Tech hosts Boston College.
(Barnhart, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
