<P>
   ATTN: PRO FOOTBALL EDITORS
</P>
<P>
   With the kickoff of the NFL season on Sunday, CoxNet will begin
posting The Journal-Constitution's two weekly NFL pages _ a preview
page and an Inside the NFL page _ every Saturday beginning this
weekend.
</P>
<P>
   The preview page will feature a standings box and a capsule
preview of the games on Sunday and the Monday night game. It will
be posted by 2 p.m. EDT each Saturday during the regular season and
is for use that Sunday. The format for this year's page will
include the equivalent of one column in ads. The AJC has asked for
the ad stack to be a strip across the bottom of the page each week,
but there is no guarantee that the ad stack will be in that
position or will be the same from week-to-week. If the capsules and
standings box are ready on Friday night, CoxNet will post the page
then without a story. This early posting will allow papers that are
using it to pull it into their systems as early as possible. In
this case, other Cox papers would have the option of waiting for
the story to move on the Sports wire or of filling the text hole
with another story, such as one about a team in their circulation
area.
</P>
<P>
   The Inside the NFL page will look much the same as the AJC's
Inside Baseball and Inside the NBA pages with conference briefs on
the outside rails and league feature stories in the middle four
columns. This page will be posted on the Cox server by 3 p.m. EDT
each Saturday during the regular season and is also for use that
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   If you have any questions, please call the CoxNet desk in
Atlanta at 404 526-5456.
</P>
