<P>
   IRELAND-CLINTON _ BELFAST, Northern Ireland _ At stop after stop
here Thursday, President Clinton won praise for shepherding the
Ireland-Northern Ireland peace accord. The congratulatory tone was
markedly different from the economic turmoil and political
uncertainty he addressed in Moscow in the first half of his
overseas trip. Developing. (Roughton, Cox News Service). EDs: To
move by 5 p.m. EDT.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   IRELAND-PEACE _ BELFAST, Northern Ireland _ Despite a
well-crafted peace agreement, all is not at peace here. The
bombings by groups determined to see the agreement fail appears to
have all but shattered what little peace there was. But President
Clinton, who arrived here in the land of his ancestors on Thursday,
will attempt to tap the hope that remains in most of the people
here. (Roughton, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   IRELAND-BOX _ DUBLIN, Ireland _ A primer on Ireland-Northern
Ireland. (Roughton, Cox News Service). EDs: To move by 5 p.m. EDT.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-POLITICS _ MOSCOW _In the wake of President Bill
Clinton's departure following a two-day summit in which he urged
Russian leaders to pull together, Russian President Boris Yeltsin
and acting Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin began making
overtures Thursday to reach a compromise with Communist and
Nationlist leaders. Meanwhile, the Russian ruble _ trading
officially for the first time in a week _ fell hard and fast
Thursday. Developing. (Holmes, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Expected to move by 3 p.m. EDT.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-ECONOMY (Analysis) _ WASHINGTON _ Russia, despite its
size _ both geographically and in population _ has an economy no
bigger than the Netherlands. That's only a fraction of the size of
the U.S. economy. Then why is that the current economic crisis
gripping the former Communist superpower is being credited with
sounding the alarm for the global economy? (Deans, Cox News
Service).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Expected to move by 4 p.m. EDT in both the (i)
International and (f) Financial categories.
