<P>
   UNDATED _ It is fitting that an African-American-oriented tour
of Texas should commence with Texarkana, which dubs itself the
``Gateway to the Southwest.'' It must be pointed out, however, that
such a tour should occur in conjunction with a trip for some other
purpose. Most Texas cities have not yet devoted as much attention
as Texarkana has to the African-American elements of their
heritage. By CECIL JOHNSON. Story will move in ``t'' travel
category. &QL; 
