<HEADLINE>
THE ANSWER TO RUSSIAN PROBLEMS
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``l'' lifestyle file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1998 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   Russian Vogue made its debut Tuesday, the same day a Page 1
headline in the San Francisco Chronicle said the country was ``Near
Breakdown.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Here's  &UR; Amber Valletta &LR;  and  &UR; Kate Moss &LR; , photographed by
 &UR; Mario Testino &LR;  in Red Square wearing scarlet-hued  &UR; Christian Dior &LR; 
ready to wear frocks,'' says a description of the Vogue cover in
the latest New York Observer. Of course, ``there is a little
economy problem,'' editorial director  &UR; Anna Harvey &LR;  told the
Observer. ``We're slightly nervous.''
</P>
<P>
   And that's not all: ``Taxis are hard to come by, and the
language barrier confronts (Vogue staff members) on the subway,''
writes the Observer's  &UR; William Norwich &LR; . ``So the editors have
found the best way to get around is walking. In flats!  &UR; Manolo &LR; 
 &UR; Blahnik &LR;  heels are carried in handheld felt shoe bags.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; IN CELEBRATION OF LOCAL TRANSIT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   With all the moaning and groaning this week about Muni
deficiencies, a major anniversary slipped quietly by: On Sept. 1,
1873, 125 years ago, the first cable car line began regular
service.
</P>
<P>
   The Clay Street Hill Railroad ran six-tenths of a mile up a
16-degree grade, recalls American Heritage magazine, between Kearny
and Jones streets. The line had been first tested in early August,
then shut down for a month while construction was completed.
</P>
<P>
   The first fare was a nickel, and the system proved an immediate
financial success.
</P>
<P>
   The cable car, invented by  &UR; Andrew Hallidie &LR;  with the help of
his draftsman,  &UR; William &LR;   &UR; Eppelsheimer &LR; , replaced horse-drawn cars.
</P>
<P>
   P.S.:  &UR; Doug Stone &LR;  has revived his 17-year-old classic lament,
``The N-Judah Blues,'' written during a 1981 crisis, before the
line went underground. Some sample lyrics:
</P>
<P>
   ``Here comes a K-Ingleside, there goes a 38-Geary/I'm asleep on
my feet getting tired and weary/And I've got a bad bad case of
those N-Judah blues. ... I see a bus on the horizon and my
confidence swells/But then that sucker turns out to be a Taraval
... Well, an F-Market street just rolled on by/I collapse on the
ground and begin to cry/I've got a bad bad case of those N-Judah
blues.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ Seven men indicted recently for allegedly plotting to
assassinate Cuban leader  &UR; Fidel Castro &LR;  are members of the
Cuban-American National Foundation, a major source of political
donations, says the Washington newspaper the Hill. The foundation
has given more than $3.2 million and supported fund-raisers for the
candidacies of lawmakers including Rep.  &UR; Dan Burton &LR; , R-Ind., and
Senators  &UR; Jesse Helms &LR; , R-N.C., and  &UR; Robert Torricelli &LR; , D-N.J.
</P>
<P>
   _ It was  &UR; Elvis Presley &LR; 's death that was remembered in Memphis
on August 16; his birthday is January 8.
</P>
<P>
   _ Massachusetts Senator  &UR; John Kerry &LR; 's wife was away Monday
night, and newspapers reported on  &LR; Wednesday that a 22-year-old
blonde was seen leaving his Boston apartment just before midnight.
``In the age of  &UR; Monica Lewinsky &LR; ,'' asked the Herald, ``is it
smart for a senator with presidential aspirations to be
entertaining attractive women when the wife is away?'' The
senator's spokesman,  &UR; Jim Jones &LR; , told the newspaper that she was
dropping off her resume.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``We all have to support each other, and we don't do that. Black
stars think that if they're not on Leno or Letterman, then they're
not making it. Their managers and agents keep them off of the black
shows. There it is, that's your major problem right there. ... All
minorities suffer.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Magic Johnson, explaining to the Electronic Urban Report why
his talk show was canceled after eight weeks. Among the black
celebrities who acknowledged to People magazine that they had
turned down guest spots: Denzel Washington, Eddie Murphy and
Vanessa Williams. Staff members for the show said Wesley Snipes,
Danny Glover and Cuba Gooding Jr. refused to appear.
</P>
</TEXT>
