 &QL; 
SAIL-MEXICO (Undated) - Not a day went by that Monte Berget, beaten
down by radiation treatment and lying exhausted in the gray
recliner, didn't think of the catamaran docked in San Diego. The
Odysseus. His family had bought the white sailboat for a year-long
trip together. Then, just before Christmas, less than a year before
they were supposed to leave, came the diagnosis of cancer. Berget
recovered from the aggressive form of cancer and the family of four
made the trip around the Baja Peninsula and drew closer, despite
dangerous storms and teenagers with attitudes. With PHOTOS. By
KELLY ETTENBOROUGH. Story will move in the ``L'' category.  &QL; 
AUTO-REVIEW (Undated) - Has it really been 10 years since the Mazda
Miata single-handedly reignited America's enthusiasm for
lightweight roadsters, years after the British had packed up their
little sports cars and gone home? Miata remains a singular
expression of sports-car virtue. Others have tried but missed the
mark.
</P>
<P>
   A recent flurry of German roadsters from BMW, Porsche and
Mercedes-Benz may eclipse the Miata in performance, but they cost
twice as much. And they probably wouldn't exist if Miata had not
paved the way. By BOB GOLFEN. Story moved in the ``L`` category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-03-98 1938EDT &QL; 
