<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Friday, Sept. 4 and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Jeremy Bagott at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   ESCAPING-LA (Los Angeles) _ A record number of Southern
Californians will hit the road this Labor Day weekend to celebrate
summer's last big hurrah. ``There's definitely more driving than
flying,'' said Randy Miller, a travel agent supervisor at AAA.
Travelers will be getting away from a weekend of Hurricane
Isis-induced rain in Southern California. By Melissa Schmitt. (Will
move in the ``n'' California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   LA-DWP-BILLS (Los Angeles) _ Today it's the heat and humidity.
Next month it will be sticker shock. That's when residents will
learn the cost of the present heat wave, from the round-the-clock
running of air conditioners and fans along with increased water
usage to keep pools filled and lawns and gardens irrigated. ``It's
hard to say for sure, but we expect customers will be paying about
15 percent more than last year at this time,'' said Steve Hansen of
Southern California Edison Co., who based his estimate on the extra
power use during this summer's record heat. By Rick Orlov and
Brooke Olson. (Will move in the ``n'' California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   LA-MAYOR-WACHS (Los Angeles) _ Perhaps it's the alignment of the
stars, but every time Los Angeles Councilman Joel Wachs becomes
acting mayor, something happens. The last time, it was the return
of the O.J. Simpson jury in his criminal trial. This time, it's the
heat wave where Wachs had to declare an unprecedented citywide heat
emergency. By Rick Orlov. (Will move in the ``n'' California news
file.)
</P>
<P>
   PACIFIC-AMERICA-SHARES (Los Angeles) _ Shares of PacificAmerica
Money Center fell approximately 33 percent Thursday as the company
warned that some of its investors had to sell at steep loses to
satisfy margin calls. The company says it's still on target for
revenue and income growth for the year.
</P>
<P>
   By Greg Wilcox. (Will move in the ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
</TEXT>
