<SLUG> BC-BBA-CANSECO-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CANSECO ADMIRES MCGWIRE'S HITTING 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By GORDON EDES  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   TORONTO _ Once, Jose Canseco shared equal billing with Mark
McGwire. No more. No matter.
</P>
<P>
   ``Mark McGwire to me is the most dominating power hitter
baseball has seen, and will ever see, in your lifetime and maybe
your children's lifetime,'' Canseco said Thursday before the
Toronto Blue Jays played the Red Sox.
</P>
<P>
   Canseco said he predicted two months ago that McGwire would
finish with 68 home runs, shattering Roger Maris's home run record
of 61.
</P>
<P>
   ``For Sammy (Sosa), this is probably a once-in-a-lifetime
thing,'' said Canseco, noting that as aggressive hitters who chase
pitches out of the strike zone, he and Sosa are much alike.
</P>
<P>
   ``Mark has a shot at the record every year. You guys don't
understand. Mark McGwire is huge. The man has 22-inch forearms. Any
other man, that's a bodybuilder's arm. His forearms are twice as
big as mine.''
</P>
<P>
   Canseco came into Thursday night's game with 37 home runs. His
personal best is 44, in 1991. Back and hamstring injuries have
restricted him, but Canseco said the biggest difference between
himself and McGwire, once his fellow Bash Brother in Oakland, is
McGwire's selectivity at the plate.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's got a tremendous eye,'' Canseco said. ``He has a
high-average-type eye and puts a swing on the ball. He has what you
call smooth power, smooth torque. Beyond everything, his eye and
technique are perfect.''
</P>
<P>
   Canseco said that when he was with the Red Sox in 1995 and the
A's came to town, he noted that McGwire was on a hot streak and
warned Boston pitchers to work around him. I said, `He's going to
eat you guys alive,''' Canseco said. ``They said, `Oh, I think I
can get him out.' I think he hit four home runs in three days.''
</P>
<P>
   McGwire hit three in one game against Red Sox pitcher Zane
Smith.
</P>
<P>
   Canseco said that when McGwire breaks the record, he plans to
call him.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'll get ahold of him,'' he said. ``To me, he's my idol. When
he breaks it, he's going to break down and cry.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
