   INTERNATIONAL NEWS (``i'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CRASH-INQUIRY (Halifax, Nova Scotia) _ Divers begin the task of
mapping the wreck site of Swissair Flight 111, which crashed at sea
Wednesday night after the pilot reported smoke in the cockpit. All
229 passengers and crew members died in the crash, including 137
Americans. By CRAGG HINES.
</P>
<P>
   CRASH-SCENE (Peggy's Cove, Nova Scotia) _ Dawn broke on one of
the most photographed spots in Canada, the fishing villages and
polished rock beaches of Nova Scotia's south shore, to reveal an
incongruous horror _ body parts and broken bits of aircraft washing
in the surf. By CRAGG HINES.
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-NIRELAND (Omagh, Northern Ireland) _ President Clinton
pays homage to the 28 people killed and 220 wounded in the Aug. 15
terrorist bombing in this Catholic community in the heart of
predominantly Protestant Ulster. He appeals to the Northern
Ireland's 1.6 million Protestants and Catholics to resolve their
differences in a new parliament that convenes Sept. 14. By STEWART
M. POWELL. (Already filed)
</P>
