<SLUG> BC-BBO-MARIS-BIO-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    The Roger Maris File
 &HT;    By Guy Curtright
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Born: Sept. 10, 1934, in Hibbing, Minn.
</P>
<P>
   Died: Dec. 14, 1985, in Houston.
</P>
<P>
   Buried: Holy Cross Catholic Cemetery, Fargo, N.D.
</P>
<P>
   Family: Married Patricia Ann Carvell, whom he met in high
school, in 1956. They had six children.
</P>
<P>
   Job after baseball: Had Anheuser-Busch distributorship in
Gainesville, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   Awards: American League MVP for Yankees in 1960 and '61.
</P>
<P>
   World Series: Played for Yankees, 1960-64, and St. Louis,
1967-68. Won World Championship four of seven times.
</P>
