<P>
   &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; AMD _  &LR; This should be the finest hour for Advanced Micro Devices
and its flamboyant founder, Jerry Sanders.
</P>
<P>
   At long last, AMD is giving its hated rival, industry leader
Intel, a run for the money. Its inexpensive K6 chip took Intel by
surprise &UR;  &LR; and is stealing some market share. But instead, AMD has
not made a profit for four successive quarters and doesn't foresee
one until the fourth quarter of this year. It's lost $120 million
so far this year. The stock is hovering near its 12-month low. By
