   BC-RUSSIA-OPPOSITION-NYT (moved on Wednesday, Sept. 2)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, Sept.
2, about the political standoff in Moscow used a word erroneously
in a description of President Boris N. Yeltsin's news conference
comment on the nomination of Viktor S. Chernomyrdin as Prime
Minster. The article should have said Mr. Yeltsin equivocated (not
prevaricated) when asked about the possibility of a compromise.
